ld did not quite yet operate in such an ideological framework. Even though the Crusades had violently pitted Christians against Muslims, there were countless contacts and a palpitable curiosity on both sides both before, during, and after those religious warfares.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aEast and WestxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aLiterature, MedievalxHistory and criticism. 0aMiddle AgesxHistoriography. 4aInterkulturalität. 4aOrientalismus. 4aOst-West-Beziehungen. 4aToleranz. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aEast-west contacts.  ainterculturality.  aorientalism.  atoleration.1 aAbate, Mark T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarajas, Courtney Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBjaï, Denis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClason, Christopher R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClassen, Albrecht, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClassen, Albrecht, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCooper, Glen M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoudert, Allison P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDarling, Linda T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHartmann, Heiko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHelmschrott, Stefanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolt, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJost, Jean E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMurray, Alan V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReza, R. Rose, econtr